cs.SE, cs.SD, cs.PL, cs.DC, cs.DL. 

This paper focuses on software engineering practices, specifically the migration of a monolithic system to microservices and the impact on Technical Debt. Therefore, cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves software development (cs.SD), programming languages (cs.PL), distributed computing (cs.DC), and deep learning (cs.DL) to some extent. However, the focus on software engineering practices makes cs.SE the most likely sub-category.
